Though the evidence is still emerging, all existing data suggests that access to estrogen or testosterone is associated with improved mental health for these kids.
There has been growing attention to the idea that some youth who start estrogen or testosterone will later choose to stop it.
State legislators need to educate themselves about these young people and their medical care before introducing legislation that will hurt them.
They need to talk to the researchers in this area, and most important, they need to bring in the transgender youth themselves.
Dr. Jack Turban (@jack_turban) is a resident physician in child and adolescent psychiatry at the Massachusetts General Hospital, where he researches the mental health of transgender youth.